Problem and Solution

We can use a range of expressions to show the relationship between a problem and its solution.

Using solution/answer + infinite (to + verb)
The solution to the issue is to spend more money.

The solution is to find a replacement.

The answer to the problem is not to waste any more money.

The answer is to keep the employee.

Using solution/answer + ing

The solution is saving more money.

The answer to your problem isn't quitting your job.

Using solved by/prevented by + ing

The problem can be solved by saving money.

This issue can be prevented by looking after our money.
